The paper deals with the Tile Assembly Model, which is a theoretical model of self-assembly. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.THEORY sub-category. The paper also involves the simulation of one tile assembly system by another, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the properties of locally consistent tile assembly systems, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and distributed systems (cs.DS).
